Run LGG and HGG survival by splicing cluster assignment

Ryan Corbett

2024

Purpose:

Runs survival analysis models using splicing cluster assignment as a predictor

Usage

Uses a wrapper function (survival_analysis) from utils folder.

Setup

Packages and functions

Load packages, set directory paths and call setup script

Rows: 1437 Columns: 6
 Column specification 
Delimiter: "\t"
chr (5): Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID, cancer_group, plot_group, molecular_subt...
dbl (1): cluster_assigned

 Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
 Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
metadata <- metadata %>%
  left_join(clusters %>% dplyr::select(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID,
                                       cluster_assigned)) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(cluster_assigned = glue::glue("cluster{cluster_assigned}")) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(cluster_assigned = fct_relevel(cluster_assigned,
                                               paste0("cluster", 1:12))) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(lgg_group = case_when(
    Histology == "Low-grade glioma" ~ "LGG",
    TRUE ~ "non-LGG"
  ))
Joining with `by = join_by(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)`

Generate log rank OS and EFS models with cluster assignment as predictor

kap_os <- survival_analysis(
  metadata  = metadata,
  ind_var = "cluster_assigned",
  test = "kap.meier",
  metadata_sample_col = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID",
  days_col = "OS_days",
  status_col = "OS_status"
)

Subset metadata for LGG, and only include clusters with >= 10 samples

lgg <- metadata %>%
  dplyr::filter(Histology == "Low-grade glioma") %>%
  dplyr::mutate(mol_sub_group = fct_relevel(mol_sub_group, c("Wildtype", "BRAF V600E", "BRAF fusion",
                                                                "Other alteration", "SEGA"
                                                                )))

retain_clusters_lgg <- lgg %>%
  count(cluster_assigned) %>%
  filter(n >= 10) %>%
  pull(cluster_assigned)

lgg <- lgg %>%
  filter(cluster_assigned %in% retain_clusters_lgg)
